{"badges":["TM5","TM6"],"preparations":[{"content":["Place bread in mixing bowl and grate <b>10 sec\/speed 10<b>. Transfer to a bowl and set aside.","Place water in mixing bowl then insert simmering basket. Add potatoes then steam <b>22 min\/Varoma\/speed 2<b>.","Place salmon fillets in Varoma dish, cover then place into position. Steam potatoes and salmon <b>8 min\/Varoma\/speed 2<b>. Set Varoma aside and remove simmering basket with aid of spatula. Discard steaming water then wash and dry mixing bowl.","Place cooked potato, 100 g reserved breadcrumbs, lemon juice, salt and pepper in mixing bowl then mix <b>10 sec\/speed 4<b>.","Flake steamed salmon into big pieces then stir into potato mix with spatula. Transfer to a bowl, allow to cool, then cover with cling film and set aside in fridge for at least 1 hour.","Once chilled, use wet hands to shape mixture into twelve patties then coat patties in remaining breadcrumbs.","Heat a non-stick frying pan with oil over a medium heat then fry fishcakes for 4-5 minutes on each side. Serve immediately with lemon wedges."]}],"ingredients":[{"title":"","content":["150 g white bread, torn in pieces","800 g water","650 g floury potatoes, peeled, diced (1 cm)","450 g fresh salmon fillets, skin removed","20 g lemon juice","¾ tsp fine sea salt","½ tsp ground black pepper","1 Tbsp sunflower oil","1 lemon, cut in wedges, for serving"]}],"id":"r83137","imageLink":"https:\/\/1.bp.blogspot.com\/-9l5TsXIwb_w\/XZVPu4yV5_I\/AAAAAAAAc78\/6UfK0fY2f3IUR5t_yafToPPPUmgRDFlogCLcBGAsYHQ\/s1600\/0_D_JJimPRGruao-zj.png","title":"Salmon Fishcakes","publishedAt":"2015-12-17T00:00:00Z","nutrition":{"protein":"29.6 g","fat":"17.2 g","uom":"per 1 portion","carbohydrates":"44.8 g","calories":"1892 kJ \/ 452 kcal"},"usefulItems":"cling film, non-stick frying pan, refrigerator, hob","hintsAndTricks":["Homemade fishcakes taste so much better than the shop-bought ones – and of course you know exactly what’s going in them, unlike many packaged ones where the fish content is very low. These make a lovely lunch or light supper with a crisp green salad and a wedge of lemon.","The mixture for these fishcakes can be made up to 24 hours in advance. Prepare to the end of step 5, then shape and cook before serving."],"basicInfo":["medium","20m","1h 50m","4 portions"]}